history.content: Read the instructions in @5366 about CS time conflicts.

I was originally #78 on the 188 waitlist, and I received an email saying I was not enrolled in the class after waitlist processing because 188 lecture has a time conflict with my 61C section at 5-6 PM. There's only 5-6 PM sections that are still open in 61C, so I can't switch that section to a different time. I submitted the conflict override Google form, but I'm concerned because I dropped 188 and tried to re-enroll into an open discussion section and am now #181 on the waitlist for CS 188. I know some people got off the waitlist for 188 by dropping & re-enrolling but I'm not sure if my time conflict and new waitlist position will affect my chances of getting into the class? Can anyone clarify this?
